cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CR 

The paper focuses on learning deep feature representations with Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for person re-identification, which is a computer vision problem. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a Domain Guided Dropout algorithm to improve the feature learning procedure, which falls under the category of machine learning algorithms. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with multimedia data (images) and evaluates the proposed method on multiple datasets, which suggests that cs.MM (Multimedia) could also be a relevant sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the effectiveness of the proposed method in terms of security applications, which could potentially fall under the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
